ZoomAlboom AI Assistant Rules

Core Architecture Principle

The Critical Separation: The Canvas layer and the IDE UI layer exist in the same Box but MUST NOT share ViewModels or StateFlows.

Canvas gestures/pans/zooms must NEVER trigger recomposition of the IDE toolbars.

IDE panel drags/expands must NEVER trigger recomposition of the Canvas.

Use Modifier.graphicsLayer for all canvas transformations.

Knowledge Base (Source of Truth)

Do NOT guess the architecture. Read these files:

🗺️ High-level: docs/architecture/overview.md

💾 Data/Room/JSON: docs/architecture/data-model.md

🎨 Canvas Math/Gestures: docs/architecture/rendering.md

🎯 Product Specs (MVP): docs/product/PRD.md

🧠 Open Decisions/Ideas: docs/MEMORY.md

Tech Stack

Kotlin 2.2+, Jetpack Compose, Room, Hilt, kotlinx.serialization, Coroutines/Flow.

Pure math functions (intersections, matrix rotation) live in core/math/ and must have 0 Android dependencies.

Follow MVI pattern (MviContract.kt).

Rules for Modifying Code

If adding a new panel, state goes into IdeViewModel (not Canvas).

If modifying node positioning, math goes into core/math/.

Heavy canvas tasks (like Viewport Culling) must run on Dispatchers.Default.
